        "title": "fix(agents): quarantine invalid runtime tool schemas",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nPruned the runtime tool-schema quarantine branch down to the assistant-turn failure path.\n\nThis now adds a pre-normalization quarantine for active runtime tools whose parameter schema cannot be serialized safely before provider normalization. Healthy sibling tools continue into provider normalization and the existing runtime-compatible projection still filters model/runtime-incompatible schemas before session creation.\n\nThe test fixtures use neutral `fuzzplugin` / `mockplugin` names.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/tool-schema-projection.test.ts src/agents/tool-schema-quarantine.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.spawn-workspace.context-engine.test.ts` passed before the latest `origin/main` rebase: 3 files, 64 tests.\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check src/agents/tool-schema-projection.ts src/agents/tool-schema-projection.test.ts src/agents/tool-schema-quarantine.ts src/agents/tool-schema-quarantine.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.spawn-workspace.context-engine.test.ts` passed.\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/agents/tool-schema-projection.ts src/agents/tool-schema-projection.test.ts src/agents/tool-schema-quarantine.ts src/agents/tool-schema-quarantine.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.spawn-workspace.context-engine.test.ts` passed.\n- `git diff --check` passed.\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` returned clean: no accepted/actionable findings.\n- AWS Crabbox `pnpm check:changed` passed before the latest `origin/main` rebase: run `run_2a737c0d190e`, lease `cbx_7680f04b0f2d` / `crimson-crayfish`, provider `aws`, command 3m11s, total 5m16s.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: A single active tool with a schema that cannot survive provider/runtime schema projection is quarantined before assistant session creation instead of crashing the whole assistant turn.\n\nReal environment tested: Local focused Vitest through `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs`; remote Linux changed gate through AWS Crabbox.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: See Verification above.\n\nEvidence after fix: Focused runner coverage shows session creation receives only the healthy sibling tool when one active tool has a non-serializable schema; projection/quarantine unit coverage verifies provider-repairable schemas are preserved and non-serializable schemas are reported.\n\nObserved result after fix: Healthy tools continue; the bad tool is reported through the existing trusted diagnostic/quarantine path.\n\nWhat was not tested: Current rebased head is blocked from rerunning the runner test and changed gate by unrelated current-main breakage in `src/infra/backoff.ts`; #88532 restores the missing shared module export. The last exact remote changed gate passed on the same patch before rebasing onto the broken main head.\n",
